  <title>Dependencies</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>CMake</keyword>
    <keyword>C++20</keyword>
    <keyword>MSVC</keyword>
    <keyword>Python</keyword>
    <keyword>Qt</keyword>
    <keyword>SoftFloat</keyword>
    <keyword>spdlog</keyword>
    <keyword>Visual Studio</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header><para styleclass="Heading1">Dependencies</para></header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">What EmulatR is built with and what it relies on at build and run time. Exact versions are to be confirmed against the current project files.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="10" colcount="3" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Component</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Role</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Notes</text></para></td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">C++20 / MSVC</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">implementation language and compiler</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">[TODO: confirm minimum toolset]</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">CMake</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">build system</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">[TODO: confirm minimum version]</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">Visual Studio 2022</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">host toolchain / IDE</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">Windows host</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">Qt 6</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">console / UI periphery only</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">the emulator core is deliberately Qt-free</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">spdlog</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">logging infrastructure</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">level macros and channels</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">Berkeley SoftFloat</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">IEEE / VAX floating-point backend</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">selectable vs a native backend</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">Python 3</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">tooling (mkdisk.py, codegen)</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">build / utility scripts</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">PuTTY / plink</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">terminal client for the console</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">any RAW-TCP client also works</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">Ghidra</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">firmware reverse-engineering</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">optional, developer-side</para></td></tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">EmulatR also depends on reference inputs it does not reimplement: the <text style="font-weight:bold;">Alpha Architecture Reference Manual</text> and the original <text style="font-weight:bold;">DEC SRM console / PALcode sources</text> (the authoritative specification and the firmware image it loads), and the <text styleclass="Code Example">AXPBox</text> emulator used as a non-authoritative differential cross-check.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
